Reasoning: The paper deals with natural language processing techniques to detect the emotion type and intensity of emotion in sexist tweets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves sentiment analysis, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves analyzing data, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
